    "body": "With `use_existing=true`, `open_floating_preview` will now reconfigure the existing window if it exists. \r\n\r\nThis allows to have a persistent LSP signature help without flickering using something along the lines:\r\n```lua\r\nfunction persistent_signature_help_update()\r\n    local help_buf = vim.b.lsp_signature_help_buf\r\n    if help_buf and vim.api.nvim_buf_is_loaded(help_buf) then\r\n        persistent_signature_help()\r\n    end\r\nend\r\n\r\nfunction persistent_signature_help()\r\n    local params = vim.lsp.util.make_position_params()\r\n    vim.lsp.buf_request(0, 'textDocument/signatureHelp', params,\r\n        function(err, result, ctx, config)\r\n            config = vim.tbl_extend('force', config or {}, {\r\n                border = 'rounded',\r\n                close_events = {\"CursorMoved\", \"InsertLeave\", \"BufHidden\"}, -- make it stay until we leave insert mode\r\n                focusable = false,\r\n                use_existing = true,\r\n                silent = true,\r\n            })\r\n            local buf, win = vim.lsp.handlers[\"textDocument/signatureHelp\"](err, result, ctx, config)\r\n            if buf then\r\n                vim.b.lsp_signature_help_buf = buf\r\n            else\r\n                if vim.api.nvim_buf_is_valid(vim.b.lsp_signature_help_buf) then\r\n                    vim.api.nvim_buf_delete(vim.b.lsp_signature_help_buf, { force = true })\r\n                    vim.b.lsp_signature_help_buf = nil\r\n                end\r\n            end\r\n        end\r\n    )\r\nend\r\n\r\n-- called in on_attach\r\nvim.cmd(string.format('autocmd CursorMovedI <buffer=%d> lua persistent_signature_help_update()', bufnr))\r\nvim.api.nvim_buf_set_keymap(bufnr, 'i', '<m-k>', '<cmd>lua persistent_signature_help()<cr>', { noremap = true })\r\n```\r\nPreviously the window would be closed, then re-opened, resulting in flickering. Reconfiguring existing window makes it look much smoother.",
